programme.title: Ramsays Kitchen Nightmares USA

programme.title: Ramsays Kitchen Nightmares USA
programme.desc: Gordon is at Sushi Ko in California. Owner Akira was a successful sushi chef at someone elses restaurant so he and his wife Lisa decided to branch out on their own. programme.title: Ramsays Kitchen Nightmares USA

programme.title: Ramsays Kitchen Nightmares USA

programme.title: Barefoot Contessa
programme.desc: Ina goes back to basics by creating fabulous favourites for the BBQ, and her bridge buddies are on standby to sample the grilled goodies.

programme.title: Barefoot Contessa
programme.desc: The delightful Ina Garten reveals her cooking tips. Herbs can really make a dish, so Ina goes back to basics with fresh herbs from the garden and she demonstrates how to make tasty, aromatic meals.

programme.title: Barefoot Contessa
programme.desc: Scrumptious cooking series with Ina Garten. Ina prepares Grecian goodies using simple ingredients that you can get a local supermarket, and her efforts double up for a surprise housewarming.

programme.title: Barefoot Contessa
programme.desc: Ina helps a friend by throwing together a quick and delicious meal thats great for a gathering of work colleagues.

programme.title: Barefoot Contessa
programme.desc: Ina cooks a meal that is every hangovers dream - a delicious grilled breakfast thats packed with warming, meaty flavours!

programme.title: Barefoot Contessa
programme.desc: Scrumptious cooking series with Ina Garten. Ina takes basic pasta recipes and turns them into truly delicious dishes that are perfect for a quick fix, food that all the family can enjoy.

programme.title: Barefoot Contessa

programme.title: Nigel Slaters Simple Suppers
programme.desc: Nigel shows how combinations of ingredients that grow in the same place at the same time often make the ideal starting point for a dish. There is no need to write down complicated recipes as Nigels unflustered style makes these feasts easy to remember. Nigel also visits local allotment holders and creates a tasty feast from the fruits of their labour.

programme.title: Nigel Slaters Simple Suppers
programme.desc: Mouth-watering chocolate cookies and crispy duck with honey and figs prove that a little bit of what you fancy does you good. Then to balance the scales, Nigel makes a couple of dishes full of clean-tasting flavours, with fresh herbs, tomatoes and crunchy greens - but whether saints or sinners, every dish will taste truly divine.

programme.title: James Martins Islands to Highlands
programme.desc: James is joined by Galton Blackiston, his pal and a top-class, Michelin-starred chef. They don diving suits to swim with seals, and hire an unusual mode of transport to take them around the islands. Galton visits a sea salt farm and delivers some back to James, who uses it to cook up some wonderful salt-baked sea bass. James finds an unusual restaurant situated in the middle of a post office, and finishes off the day cooking roast duck by a stunning seashore.

programme.title: James Martins Islands to Highlands
programme.desc: James returns to one of his favourite places in the UK: the beautiful county of Cornwall. Joining him is his close pal and Michelin-starred chef Galton Blackiston. During their trip they discover some world-class Cornish ice cream, and Galton visits Newlyn fish market to pick up some Cornish cod. James cooks the cod along with Cornish oysters and a warm tartare sauce. They both round off the day with a painting challenge on Sennen beach, where they try out their oil painting skills.

programme.title: Secrets of the Curry Kitchen

programme.title: Nadiyas Simple Spices

programme.title: Nadiyas Simple Spices
programme.desc: Nadiya Hussain serves up deliciously treaty meals to rival any takeaway. These four flavour packed dishes - a smoky aubergine pizza, a spicy spin on egg fried rice, a speedy chicken jalfrezi and kulfi ice cream biscuit bars.

programme.title: Nadiyas Simple Spices
programme.desc: Nadiya shares family favourites perfect for any occasion: an authentic chicken curry infused with aromatic whole spices that has been passed down the generations of Nadiyas family, a cumin and dill-laced samosa, a quick, delicious tangy tomato prawn dish, and her sons favourite cake, a sweet cardamom traybake. And food writer Ping Coombes shares her passion for passing down the flavours of her ancestral cooking to her family, with star anise taking a starring role.

programme.title: Nadiyas Simple Spices

programme.title: Great British Food Revival
programme.desc: Top BBC chefs are on a mission to popularise traditional British produce. In this first episode, Michel Roux Jr campaigns for the return of the artisan baker to the UK high street and shares his own unique recipes to show how easy and rewarding home baking can be. Next, the Hairy Bikers are on the case of the British cauliflower, determined to show that not only is it nutritious, but versatile and tasty.

programme.title: Great British Food Revival
programme.desc: Chef James Martin is reviving the British apple. Forced off the supermarket shelves by identikit fruit that have been shipped in from as far away as New Zealand and Chile, James is determined to show off the qualities of home-grown apples. Chef Matt Tebbutt is on the case of mutton. Due to cheap imports of lamb, mutton has lost its place as a family staple, but Matt is determined to win back its reputation.

programme.title: Great British Food Revival
programme.desc: Ainsley Harriott starts a campaign for the revival of British honey. With bees under threat from disease and a lack of awareness of our native honey production, Ainsley finds out how we can all play our part in its revival. Then its time for Michelin starred chef Glynn Purnell to ride to the rescue of British cheese. Cheap foreign imports and misleading labelling means that Glynn has his work cut out for him.

programme.title: Great British Food Revival
programme.desc: Gary Rhodes wants us all to appreciate the virtues of the British tomato. Unlike the Italian and Spanish, we view the tomato as a year round product and ignore the British growing season when our own fruit is at its best. Elsewhere, Angela Hartnett looks at why crab is so unloved in Britain, when our coastal waters are teeming with sweet tasting brown and spider crab.

programme.title: Full Steam Ahead
programme.desc: The team visit Beamish in County Durham to explore how the railway companies soon recognised that there was money to be made in moving people, rather than just stone, coal and iron. The comfort of the early passenger wagons are put to the test on one of the earliest steam trains, and Ruth finds out how people were moving further than ever before.

programme.title: Full Steam Ahead
programme.desc: The team find out how the railways transformed the British diet, rescuing a nation that was struggling to feed itself. Putting theory into practice Alex and Peter load a flock of sheep onto a train, discovering how the mass transportation of livestock by rail transformed the quality and quantity of meat available to Victorian consumers. This new capability gave birth to the traditional British roast.

programme.title: The Bill

Stuart and Jo discover her portfolio; the pictures inside were all taken by photographer Jeff Slade. He is arrested for murder, but then a blood-soaked T-shirt seems to implicate the dead womans fiance, Darrell Crow. Elsewhere, Emma and Beth investigate a burglary - and uncover a case of blackmail.

programme.title: The Bill
programme.desc: Smithy is Acting Inspector in Ginas absence and deploys the troops at the funeral of murdered supermodel Cindy Statham. He manages to escape and knocks Beth unconscious when she tries to reason with him. Elsewhere, Smithy investigates an armed robbery at a building society.

programme.title: The Bill
programme.desc: Larry Franks withdraws his confession to murdering Cindy Statham and Jo reopens the case believing him to be innocent, but when Neil and Grace interview him again, he clams up when his request to speak to Jo is denied. Elsewhere, Mickey investigates a robbery and is stunned when his friend admits to the burglaries.

programme.title: Ambulance Australia
programme.desc: In the Sydney Control Centre, a triple zero call is answered every 27 seconds. Paramedics Josh and Sophie are rushing under lights and sirens to a warehouse in Sydneys west, where a forklift has rolled over, trapping a worker. In Liverpool, we meet paramedics Samantha and Tammie, whose first job is a car accident in which a pregnant womans waters have broken on impact.

programme.title: Ambulance Australia
programme.desc: The high volume of Saturday night calls contributes to severe delays at Liverpool Hospital, leading to a shortage in ambulances and long wait times for patients. Out on the streets, paramedics struggle to free patients from the wreckage of a horrific motor vehicle accident, deal with an intoxicated man with injuries, and worry about the possibility of a traumatic brain injury.

programme.title: Ambulance Australia
programme.desc: A call taker tries to revive a hanging patient over the phone when the family has already given up, and a heart attack turns into a race against the clock. A double stabbing pushes the NSW Ambulance services to their limits, while an elderly patient in late-stage emphysema shares her most intimate stories.

programme.title: The Supervet
programme.desc: Veterinarian Noel Fitzpatrick is one of Englands top animal doctors and the subject of 2010 documentary programme `The Bionic Vet, which showcased some of the work done at his Surrey clinic. On `The Supervet Fitzpatrick and his staff treat some of the countrys hardest-to-cure pets with cutting-edge treatments and surgery. The programme tells the emotional stories of the pets, their owners and the passionate team that push the boundaries of veterinary medicine to save the animals from life-threatening conditions.

programme.title: The Supervet
programme.desc: Supervet Noel Fitzpatrick returns to help more animals with hard-to-cure ailments. Noel and his team help a giant Newfoundland puppy called Lola. Also, a golden Labrador needs a bionic solution for a deformed front paw.

programme.title: One Born: What Happened Next?
programme.desc: This episode catches up with 30-year-old Kerry and 39-year-old Paul. After a lot of screaming from Kerry, and a few firms words from her midwife, baby Jamie, their second child, was born. Nine months on, his older sister Emily is exhibiting classic signs of sibling rivalry. Also, find out how Phil and Lydia have got on since their child was born.

programme.title: Life
